<div id="what-is-a-marketing-proposal"></div>
<h2>What is a marketing proposal?</h2>
<p>A marketing proposal is a written document that an agency/marketer provides to a client to communicate the details of a given project or service. Those details include everything the client and stakeholder need to decide whether to sign the contract.</p>
<p>Like any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/03/11/business-proposals">good business proposal</a>, the marketing proposal comes after a discovery session where the agency/marketer collects all of the information they need to formulate the strategy, timeline, and pricing.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want to know how your agency stacks up to the competition? Download our free report: <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite2023AgencyIndustryReport.html?cid=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_StateoftheAgency2023_Download&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=web&amp;utm_campaign=2023SOTA&amp;utm_content=compare_pricing&amp;utm_term=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_StateoftheAgency2023_Download&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=incontent_links&amp;utm_content=2023SOTA">State of the Digital Marketing Agency</a></p>
<div id="why-marketing-proposals-are-important"></div>
<h2>Why you need a marketing proposal</h2>
<p>So we just covered the basic definition and purpose of a marketing proposal, but there‚Äôs more to it than just information. It‚Äôs part art, part science. The science part is the logistics, quantifiable goals, metrics, timelines, and deliverables. The art part is how you present it, and how you use it to bring about the intangibles in your clients, like excitement about success, confidence in your services, and relief that their problem will be solved.</p>
<p>A marketing proposal:</p>
<ul>
<li>Provides all of the information needed for a prospective client to confidently say yes.</li>
<li>Shows how you can organize and convey information in a compelling way.</li>
<li>Gives you a chance to <a href="https://www.proposify.com/proposal-templates/marketing-proposal-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener">stand out from competitors</a> and also show that you‚Äôve listened closely and thought through the details.</li>
<li>Highlights your qualifications and past successes.</li>
<li>Helps you to map out the project and stay accountable.</li>
<li>Protects you from scope creep and unpaid invoices.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-benefits.webp" alt="how to write a marketing proposal - why you need a marketing proposal - example of piece of marketing proposal" width="710" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78438" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-benefits.webp 710w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-benefits-480x405.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 710px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.proposify.com/proposal-templates/marketing-proposal-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<div id="what-to-include-in-marketing-proposal"></div>
<h2>What to include in a marketing proposal</h2>
<p>What you include in your marketing proposal will depend on your services, your client, and your industry, but here is a list that you can pick and choose from:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cover page:</strong> Your first impression! Make it bold, attractive, and catered to your client‚Äôs brand feel.</li>
<li><strong>Executive summary:</strong> Summarizes the overarching problem, goal, and solution; the big picture concept that will get stakeholders to want to listen in on the rest of the presentation.</li>
<li><strong>Table of contents:</strong> A small but necessary detail to help your client navigate through the content on their own.</li>
<li><strong>Goals:</strong> What the client is striving to achieve. These should include both the project goals as well as how those goals fit into greater organizational and <a href="https://www.proposify.com/proposal-templates/marketing-proposal-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing goals</a>. Ideally, these goals are measurable.</li>
<li><strong>Challenges:</strong> What‚Äôs getting in the way of achieving those goals. Your client will know most of their challenges but you may also be able to identify additional ones during the discovery session.</li>
<li><strong>Solutions:</strong> The <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/03/best-marketing-strategies">marketing strategies</a> you will implement to solve for the challenges and goals.</li>
<li><strong>Scope of work:</strong> The tactics of the strategies, as well as timeframes and other operational details.</li>
<li><strong>Outcome:</strong> The deliverables of each phase or strategy, how they tie back to the core goals, and any additional benefits.</li>
<li><strong>Pricing: </strong>The cost to the client fully broken out.¬† May have a few options to choose from. Provides clear return on investment</li>
<li><strong>Working with us:</strong> A look into the team members, your culture, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/09/company-core-values">values</a>. Keep it focused on what value this delivers to the client.</li>
<li><strong>Why us?</strong> Any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/07/19/customer-testimonial-examples">testimonials</a>, awards, success metrics, special skills, or social proof that make you especially fit for the job.</li>
<li><strong>Contract:</strong> The terms and conditions and any other legalese you need to include. Try to keep this as easy to read as possible.</li>
</ul>
<div id="tips-for-writing-marketing-proposal"></div>
<h2>Tips for creating a winning marketing proposal</h2>
<p>It‚Äôs not just the information that goes into your proposal‚Äîbut also how you gather, present, and deliver that information‚Äîthat matters. Here are some tips on creating marketing proposals that win over clients.</p>
<h3>Do your prep work</h3>
<p>The proposal should come after a thorough discovery session where you get all of the information you need. Take detailed notes so your proposal doesn‚Äôt just satisfy their needs, but reflects that you listen carefully and care about and will cater to their individual preferences.</p>
<p>Information to gather in the discovery session:</p>
<ul>
<li>Goals and challenges (short and long-term)</li>
<li>The problem and the source of the problem</li>
<li>Past/existing strategies/successes/failures (including other agencies)</li>
<li>Existing metrics/What will success look like</li>
<li>Priorities</li>
<li>Emotions involved (frustrations, desires, pain points)</li>
<li>The personalities and work styles of the client‚Äôs team members</li>
<li>Their timeline, budget, stakeholders</li>
<li>Their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">target audience</a>, brand messaging, and customer journey</li>
</ul>
<h3>Do additional research</h3>
<p>Your client knows their business best, but you should still do additional research both before and after the discovery session. Gather as much as you can about the client before the session so you can demonstrate your diligence, alleviate them from having to educate you, and free up more time for the more nuanced details.</p>
<p>Do research after the session, on the market, competition, and anything pertinent to the session. This will allow you to add stats and examples to your proposal that can strengthen your case and further <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-demonstrate-value-to-your-customers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">demonstrate your value</a>.</p>
<h3>Make it easy to read and visual</h3>
<p>This is the same tip I give for <a href="https://www.usehatchapp.com/blog/hvac-service-contract-templates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">service businesses in their service contracts</a>. Don‚Äôt write in complex or formal language to try and impress your client! Keep it <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/05/conversational-tone">conversational </a>and easy to read. Use terms they use, and constantly refer back to the problems and goals they are focused on. Also, visualize wherever you can, such as with timelines:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-timeline.webp" alt="how to write a marketing proposal - example of timelines in marketing proposal" width="936" height="545" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78447" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-timeline.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-timeline-480x279.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Keep it client-focused</h3>
<p>While a marketing proposal is an opportunity to show your value and set yourself apart from competitors, it needs to stay focused on the client, not you. Any time you highlight something great about your business, be sure to connect it back to what value that provides for the clent.</p>
<h3>Walk through it with them</h3>
<p>Don‚Äôt just email the proposal over to your client. Set a time to meet and walk through it together. This will ensure the proposal communicates the information and messaging that you intended and ensures the client sees the details in your work. You can then send the proposal after the meeting and give them time to digest it, think it over, and come up with any other questions before signing.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteGrowYourMarketingAgency.html?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Agency_StrategiestoGrowYourAgency_Download">The 6 Absolute Best Strategies to Grow Your Digital Marketing Agency</a></p>
<div id="marketing-proposal-templates"></div>
<h2>Marketing proposal templates</h2>
<p>Here are some marketing proposal templates from a range of resources, including marketing agencies, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/12/07/proposal-generator">online proposal generators</a>, and marketing blogs.</p>
<h3>1. Indeed‚Äôs text-only marketing proposal</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/career-development/how-to-write-a-marketing-proposal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Indeed‚Äôs marketing proposal template</a> is nice and basic. It‚Äôs text-only with brackets and guidance on what to put into the brackets. While there is no design help here, Indeed provides tips, best practices, and examples, making it great for marketers or agencies looking to come up with an effective proposal copywriting framework.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-indeed.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from indeed" width="389" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78443" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-indeed.webp 389w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-indeed-195x300.webp 195w" sizes="(max-width: 389px) 100vw, 389px" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cover page</li>
<li>Table of contents</li>
<li>Executive summary</li>
<li>Project overview
<ul>
<li>Problem statement</li>
<li>Solution statement</li>
<li>Scope of work</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Investment
<ul>
<li>Cost estimate</li>
<li>Contract and payment terms</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Timeline</li>
<li>Project team and introductions</li>
<li>Case study</li>
<li>Agreement and signatures</li>
</ul>
<h3>2. Fool.com‚Äôs marketing proposal example</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.fool.com/the-ascent/small-business/email-marketing/articles/marketing-proposal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fool.com‚Äôs marketing proposal template</a> also isn‚Äôt downloadable, but the post itself is formatted as a marketing proposal, with a definition and example for each section. This template is ideal for an agency or marketer who is just starting out and unsure of what to put into a proposal.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-fool.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from fool.com" width="936" height="381" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78441" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-fool.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-fool-480x195.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Executive summary</li>
<li>Challenges/objectives</li>
<li>Strategy/solution</li>
<li>Scope of work</li>
<li>Financials</li>
<li>Terms and conditions</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. HubSpot‚Äôs downloadable marketing proposal template</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.hubspot.com/business-templates/marketing-proposal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HubSpot‚Äôs marketing proposal template</a> is a downloadable template that you can customize. While it doesn‚Äôt include example text, it provides the format and tips for each section. It also offers plenty of opportunities to pitch and distinguish your business while still making it about the customer. This is a good proposal for a service that is well-versed in proposals but wants to improve the organization and/or give it a little extra marketing pep.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-hubspot.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from hubspot" width="487" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78442" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-hubspot.webp 487w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-hubspot-480x591.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 487px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>About us (services you provide, team, relevant skills)</li>
<li>Project scope (summary, proposed solution, phases/deliverables)</li>
<li>Projected outcome</li>
<li>Project schedule</li>
<li>Contact us</li>
<li>Contract and signatures</li>
<li>Appendix (past work, portfolio, samples)</li>
<li>Additional Materials</li>
</ul>
<h3>4. Pitch‚Äôs marketing proposal slide deck templates</h3>
<p><a href="https://pitch.com/templates/Marketing-Proposal-6BazfH6AcfE45PJr5i5oE3qM" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pitch</a> is a free online presentation builder for a range of industries, so you won‚Äôt get much marketing advice but you will get attractive, predesigned slides, interactive features, animations, and more. It‚Äôs best for marketers who have their proposal copywriting down pat and are looking for inspiration on ways to display it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-pitch.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from pitch" width="663" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78445" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-pitch.webp 663w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-pitch-480x433.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 663px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template contains example slides for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Introduction</li>
<li>Agenda</li>
<li>Customer personas</li>
<li>Competitor analysts</li>
<li>Market share</li>
<li>Charts (line and bar)</li>
<li>Opportunities</li>
<li>Total budget</li>
<li>Timeline</li>
<li>Questions</li>
<li>Thank you</li>
</ul>
<h3>5. Jotform‚Äôs esignature marketing proposal builder</h3>
<p>Jotform is an esignature platform with a WSWYG design editor. With <a href="https://www.jotform.com/sign/232595865746069" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Jotfrom‚Äôs marketing proposal template</a>, the core content is already in place, you just have to fill in the blanks. You can also make changes to the master template and customze the design to your branding. In addition, you can use Jotform itself to share the proposal via email and collect e-signatures from any device. It doesn‚Äôt include examples and it‚Äôs pretty basic, so this is best for marketers who know what makes an effective proposal and just need a tool to make it look great and/or offer esigning.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-jotform.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from jotform" width="431" height="599" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78444" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-jotform.webp 431w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-jotform-216x300.webp 216w" sizes="(max-width: 431px) 100vw, 431px" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template contains:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cover page</li>
<li>Cover letter</li>
<li>Background</li>
<li>Analysis of current state and objectives</li>
<li>Length of contract</li>
<li>Estimated costs and expenses</li>
<li>Terms and conditions</li>
<li>Signature</li>
</ul>
<h3>6. Proposify‚Äôs marketing proposal</h3>
<p>As an online proposal builder tool, <a href="https://www.proposify.com/proposal-templates/marketing-proposal-template" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Proposify‚Äôs marketing proposal template</a> takes the cake in the way of aesthetics but does not come with much guidance in the way of what to write and how to write it. Like the above two templates, it‚Äôs best for marketers who can write effective proposal copy and just need a way to design it.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-proposify.webp" alt="marketing proposal template from proposify" width="429" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78446" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-proposify.webp 429w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-proposify-215x300.webp 215w" sizes="(max-width: 429px) 100vw, 429px" /></p>
<p>This marketing proposal template contains:</p>
<ul>
<li>Overview and goals</li>
<li>Scope of services</li>
<li>Timeframe</li>
<li>Your investment</li>
<li>Why us</li>
<li>Our team</li>
<li>Case study</li>
<li>Contract</li>
<li>Signature</li>
</ul>
<h3>7. Canva‚Äôs marketing proposal template gallery</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.canva.com/proposals/templates/marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Canva‚Äôs marketing proposal template gallery</a> offers tons of attractive designs to choose from. The templates are in portrait style but you change the dimensions to be landscape for a slide deck style. Some of them even have example text to help.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-canva.webp" alt="marketing proposal templates from canva" width="936" height="443" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78440" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-canva.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/marketing-proposal-template-canva-480x227.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Start winning more clients with these marketing proposal templates</h2>
<p>As I said, a marketing proposal is a piece of marketing collateral in and of itself. And it‚Äôs part art, part science. With the right balance of information and metrics with design and delivery, a good proposal can win over the client and set the stage for a successful project.</p>
