</article>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>I‚Äôm now $56 poorer and 10 pounds heavier and I have remarketing to thank.</em></p>
<p>All these things are fixable and getting it right can turn PPC into a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/20/google-ads-for-lead-generation">lead generation machine</a>!</p>
<h2>One last note before you go forth and sell PPC to clients‚Ä¶</h2>
<p>We‚Äôve been focusing on how to win new PPC business, but as a final caveat, I want to stress that it‚Äôs also important to know when to say <em>no</em> to a new client. Be sure to check out my <a href="/blog/ws/2014/07/24/adwords-agency-client-red-flags">top ten red flags</a> that you‚Äôre dealing with a client who is going to be a nightmare or is going to churn. Just say no, it‚Äôs not worth your time!</p>
<p>Here are the 9 ways to sell more clients on PPC:</p>
<ol>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Follow up with EVERY lead</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Go after low-hanging fruit</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Talk about how PPC complements other marketing strategies</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Create a referral program</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Partner with complementary agencies or businesses</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Understand the importance of the first outreach attempt</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Don‚Äôt lose the art of the follow-up</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Develop a plan that optimizes your reps‚Äô time</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Know how to respond to common objections</span></li>
</ol>
